            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/R2475Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>blanched</strong> <strong>peas </strong>to a bowl and <strong>microwave</strong> for 1 min, or until hot and cooked with a bite</p><p>Add the <strong>cooked peas</strong> to a <strong>food processor</strong> along with a knob of<strong> butter</strong>, 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong>, the <strong>chopped dill</strong>, a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and the <strong>juice</strong> of <strong>1</strong> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2]</span> <strong>lemon wedge<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Pulse until blitzed but not smooth – these are your <strong>mushy peas</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
